---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';

const posts: Record<string, { title: string; date: string; content: string }> = {
  goodness: {
    title: 'GOODNESS',
    date: 'March 19, 2025',
    content: `
      <p>Kevin White shares four daily affirmations centered on God's goodness:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>God, you are GOOD</li>
        <li>You are GOOD to me</li>
        <li>You are GOOD at being God</li>
        <li>God is GOOD and does GOOD</li>
      </ol>
      <p>The post emphasizes recognizing God's goodness rather than focusing solely on material supply. As Steven Furtick says: <em>"Perhaps you don't have a supply problem, you have a sight problem."</em></p>
      <h2>Seeing God's Goodness</h2>
      <p>Through Scripture — Psalms, Romans, Jeremiah — we see God's intentional plans for good outcomes in believers' lives.</p>
      <h2>Practical Steps</h2>
      <p>To preserve awareness of goodness: search, remember, count, record, protect, proclaim, and share it. God's kindness convicts, purifies, cleanses, and transforms people.</p>
      <p>Commit to recognizing God's goodness consistently. Watch The Kevin White Show on YouTube every Tuesday at 10 AM for weekly encouragement.</p>
    `,
  },
  faithfulness: {
    title: 'FAITHFULNESS',
    date: 'March 19, 2025',
    content: `
      <p>Kevin White shares a message about God's faithfulness and encourages modeling that same faithfulness through three commitments:</p>
      <h2>Praise</h2>
      <p>Continuous praise should override negative emotions like worry, doubt, and fear. "I will praise the LORD at all times. I will constantly speak his praises" (Psalms 34:1-2).</p>
      <h2>Prayer</h2>
      <p>Prayer is the "information technology system" for business success — the essential connection between God's kingdom and earthly operations. <strong>Prayer up — company up. Prayer down — company down.</strong></p>
      <h2>Sales</h2>
      <p>Sales reframed as a spiritual calling rather than purely commercial activity. Sharing God's message and supporting organizations — churches, nonprofits, businesses — all require sales efforts.</p>
      <p>Kevin forecasts coming abundance but warns against allowing prosperity to diminish commitment to these three practices. Character development and unwavering dedication to kingdom impact are essential.</p>
    `,
  },
  multiply: {
    title: 'MULTIPLY',
    date: 'March 10, 2025',
    content: `
      <p>The article explores "multiply" as a divine principle woven throughout biblical history, beginning with creation and continuing through Jesus's ministry.</p>
      <p>God embedded multiplication into creation itself. <em>"Be fruitful and multiply. Fill the earth and govern it."</em> (Genesis 1:27-30)</p>
      <h2>Abraham's Legacy</h2>
      <p>God promised Abraham his descendants would bless all families on earth, establishing multiplication as a spiritual inheritance.</p>
      <h2>Jesus's Example</h2>
      <p>Jesus demonstrated multiplication through calling twelve disciples, performing miracles of abundance, and commissioning followers to spread the gospel.</p>
      <h2>The Disciples' Mission</h2>
      <p>After the resurrection, followers received the Holy Spirit and became witnesses "to the ends of the earth."</p>
      <p>Multiplication is not optional but a foundational spiritual principle passed from generation to generation. This divine mandate persists despite human failings and continues shaping believers' purpose today.</p>
    `,
  },
  joy: {
    title: 'JOY',
    date: 'February 24, 2025',
    content: `
      <p>The post explores joy through a biblical lens, identifying three distinct types:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Emotional</strong> — an immediate feeling state</li>
        <li><strong>Positional</strong> — a lasting character trait</li>
        <li><strong>Spiritual</strong> — fruit of the Holy Spirit</li>
      </ol>
      <h2>Language Origins</h2>
      <p>In Hebrew, <em>sason</em> describes sudden exuberance — like a game-winning moment. In Greek, <em>simcha</em> represents sustained joy connected to purpose and shared community experience.</p>
      <h2>God's Expectation</h2>
      <p>Serving God without joy displeases Him. Deuteronomy 28:47-48 warns against joyless service.</p>
      <h2>Active Expression</h2>
      <p>"Rejoice" functions as the active demonstration of joy's internal position. Jesus reportedly used joy-centered greetings rather than standard salutations.</p>
      <p>Joy is an unshakeable divine gift independent of personal circumstances, transformative for spiritual practice and daily living.</p>
    `,
  },
  rewarded: {
    title: 'REWARDED',
    date: 'February 18, 2025',
    content: `
      <p>Kevin White explores the biblical concept of God's rewards for faithful followers, citing passages from 2 Chronicles and Hebrews that assure believers of divine compensation.</p>
      <p><strong>"If God says he will reward us for our faith then God will reward us!"</strong></p>
      <p>Rewards ultimately belong to Jesus rather than individuals. Believers function as stewards who multiply kingdom impact. When the Father rewards His Son through us, we respond with worship and gratitude.</p>
      <h2>Personal Testimony</h2>
      <p>At his high school awards ceremony, Kevin's name was unexpectedly called three times — for $1,500, $3,000, and $4,000 scholarships — totaling his first year's tuition. Though neither parent attended college, Kevin became the only sibling to do so, viewing this as divine affirmation of his faith commitment.</p>
      <p>Expect God's rewards without dictating how or when they arrive.</p>
    `,
  },
  paths: {
    title: 'PATHS',
    date: 'February 10, 2025',
    content: `
      <p><em>"He renews my strength. He guides me along right PATHS, bringing honor to his name."</em> (Psalms 23:3, NLT)</p>
      <h2>Six Standards for Spirit Media</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Know and live out God's Word</li>
        <li>Pray with Jesus' authority for His Kingdom to come</li>
        <li>Praise Him at all times</li>
        <li>Boast only on the Lord</li>
        <li>Pursue every sales lead He brings</li>
        <li>Identify, address, and eliminate waste</li>
      </ol>
      <p>He warns against a recurring biblical pattern: people become desperate for God, receive blessings, stop depending on Him, and eventually rebel — a cycle that repeats throughout Scripture.</p>
      <h2>Purity Proceeds Prosperity</h2>
      <p>Connecting God's kingdom principles to multiplication and stewardship. PATHS protect, guide, and provide for believers. <strong>"God's guidance is God's provision."</strong></p>
      <p>Pass these standards to future generations, maintaining clarity around both the "what" and "why" of organizational values.</p>
    `,
  },
  revelation: {
    title: 'REVELATION',
    date: 'January 31, 2025',
    content: `
      <p>Kevin White shares his personal journey with understanding biblical revelation. He recalls childhood fear of the Book of Revelation, but after praying at 17 — <em>"God if there is more to you than I realize, I want to know it"</em> — his perspective transformed fundamentally.</p>
      <h2>What God Reveals</h2>
      <p>Identity, purpose, calling, strategy, freedom, and guidance for daily decisions. Scripture references include 1 Corinthians 2:10-16, Hebrews 1:1-4, and Acts 2:17-18.</p>
      <h2>How We Receive Revelation</h2>
      <p>Through worship, scripture study, prayer, dreams, conversations, and unexpected moments.</p>
      <h2>Ground Rules</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Personal revelation precedes revelation for others</li>
        <li>All revelation points toward God</li>
        <li>Authentic revelation aligns with Scripture</li>
      </ul>
    `,
  },
  fight: {
    title: 'FIGHT!',
    date: 'June 20, 2024',
    content: `
      <p>Kevin White discusses spiritual fighting in both personal and professional contexts. His company is fighting to find the right people, leverage tools like Amazon, Google, and YouTube for the glory of God, be effective, and be profitable.</p>
      <p>Spiritual battles are not physical conflicts between people, but internal struggles against evil. <em>"Fight the good fight for the true faith."</em> (1 Timothy 6:12)</p>
      <h2>Five Principles</h2>
      <p>Truth, righteousness, peace, faith, and salvation.</p>
      <h2>Three Weapons</h2>
      <p>God's Word, prayer in the Spirit, and persistence.</p>
      <p><strong>"I want to encourage you to be a FIGHTER. Let God FIGHT through you. The battle belongs to the Lord. The battle has already been won!"</strong></p>
    `,
  },
  boasting: {
    title: 'BOASTING',
    date: 'June 20, 2024',
    content: `
      <p><em>"What do you have that God hasn't GIVEN you? And if everything you have is from God, why BOAST as though it were not a GIFT?"</em> (1 Corinthians 4:7, NLT)</p>
      <p>Nothing is owned outright — everything originates from God through Jesus. Possessions, jobs, success, and projects should not fuel personal pride since they represent unearned blessings.</p>
      <h2>The Gideon Account</h2>
      <p>In Judges 7:2-24, God deliberately reduced Gideon's army from 32,000 to 300 soldiers. The reduction prevented the Israelites from attributing victory to their military strength rather than recognizing divine intervention. Despite overwhelming numerical disadvantage, the smaller force prevailed through God's power.</p>
      <h2>Key Principles</h2>
      <p>God multiplies through subtraction: pruning, fasting, tithing, and worship. Seeking God's kingdom requires personal denial (Matthew 6:33, John 12:24).</p>
      <p>Boast solely in the Lord (Psalm 34:2, 1 Corinthians 1:29-31).</p>
    `,
  },
  succeed: {
    title: 'SUCCEED!',
    date: 'June 20, 2024',
    content: `
      <p><strong>Help others succeed and you will succeed too.</strong></p>
      <p><em>"The welfare of the city will determine your welfare."</em> (Jeremiah 29:7). This extends to company loyalty — employees should pray for leadership and organizational success, as individual prosperity depends on the institution's welfare.</p>
      <h2>The Ten Commandments Framework</h2>
      <p>Exodus 20:1-17 reveals that genuine success requires consideration beyond oneself.</p>
      <h2>Business Application</h2>
      <p>At Spirit Media, Kevin calls his team to embrace loyalty, shared vision, honesty, and waste elimination. He references Coca-Cola Consolidated's mission emphasizing God, service, excellence, and profitability — an integrated approach rather than profit-only focus.</p>
      <p>Kevin invites employees toward ownership mentality: client success enables company success, which enables employee success. Mutual interdependence ensures all parties benefit collectively.</p>
    `,
  },
  relationships: {
    title: 'RELATIONSHIPS',
    date: 'June 20, 2024',
    content: `
      <p>Business success depends on strong relationships and results, grounded in Matthew 22:36-40 where Jesus emphasizes loving God and others as the greatest commandments.</p>
      <h2>God's Model for Relationships</h2>
      <p>God demonstrates the supreme importance of relationships by becoming human. <em>"The Word became human and made his home among us."</em> (John 1:14)</p>
      <h2>Business Application</h2>
      <p>At Spirit Media, Kevin's company prioritizes understanding clients by studying them, representing them authentically, and knowing their audiences. <strong>"The most beloved action in any relationship is to be heard."</strong></p>
      <h2>Listening as Leadership</h2>
      <p>Adopt the Golden Rule (Matthew 7:12) and become a "client in your own company" by genuinely listening to customer needs rather than speaking only to them.</p>
      <p>God listens to human voices. Leaders should identify with client problems and let clients determine when relationships are healthy.</p>
    `,
  },
};

export function getStaticPaths() {
  return [
    'goodness', 'faithfulness', 'multiply', 'joy', 'rewarded',
    'paths', 'revelation', 'fight', 'boasting', 'succeed', 'relationships',
  ].map(slug => ({ params: { slug } }));
}

const { slug } = Astro.params;
const post = posts[slug];
if (!post) return Astro.redirect('/blog');
---

<Layout title={`${post.title} — Kevin White`} description={`Read "${post.title}" by Kevin White`}>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <meta property="og:type" content="article" />
    <meta property="article:author" content="Kevin White" />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BlogPosting",
      "headline": post.title,
      "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Kevin White" },
      "publisher": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Kevin White", "url": "https://kevinwhite.us" },
      "url": `https://kevinwhite.us/blog/${slug}`,
      "datePublished": post.date
    })}></script>
  </Fragment>

  <main>
    <!-- Post Header -->
    <section class="bg-[var(--color-bg-warm)] section-padding">
      <div class="container-site max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-gold)] no-underline hover:text-[var(--color-gold-dark)] mb-6">&larr; Back to Magazines</a>
        <h1>{post.title}</h1>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-light)]">
          <span>By <strong class="text-[var(--color-text)]">Kevin White</strong></span>
          <span>&middot;</span>
          <span>{post.date}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Post Content -->
    <section class="bg-white section-padding">
      <div class="container-site max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="prose-content" set:html={post.content} />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="bg-[var(--color-bg-dark)] text-white section-padding">
      <div class="container-site text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-2">Watch The Kevin White Show</p>
        <h2 class="text-white mb-6">Every Tuesday at 10 AM on YouTube</h2>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@KevinWhiteTV" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-gold">Watch Now</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose-content :global(h2) {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .prose-content :global(h3) {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .prose-content :global(p) {
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .prose-content :global(ol),
  .prose-content :global(ul) {
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  .prose-content :global(li) {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .prose-content :global(strong) {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .prose-content :global(em) {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
</style>
